From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 12:20:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX-015 Route B rd_native gpu_culling
 in-frame compute cull

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040..0045. First rd_native pass that itself issues
RD::buffer_clear (the count dwords + visibility bitmask). Drives the MAIN
RenderingDevice's buffer_clear -> compute dispatch -> native indirect-draw chain
so it is fully visible to the draw graph's ResourceTracker, structurally
avoiding the shim path's device-removal hazard (its side-channel dispatch was
invisible to the graph, which transitioned the command buffer to
INDIRECT_ARGUMENT while a side-channel UAV write was still in flight).

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_gpu_culling_rd_native(RID transforms, RID commands, RID visibility,
  const uint8_t *frustum_planes, uint32_t planes_bytes, const uint8_t *b0,
  uint32_t b0_bytes, uint32_t instance_count, uint32_t surface_count, uint32_t
  command_stride_dwords, uint32_t instance_count_dword_index, uint32_t
  visibility_bytes). Takes Godot RID handles (not native ID3D12Resource*).
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings
  (.../passes/gpu_culling/backend int default 0 and .../rd_container_path),
  INDEPENDENT of the four shim gpu_culling settings (0027-0029), which are
  untouched.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_gpu_culling_rd_native
  override + a self-owned 96-byte frustum-planes SSBO (the t1
  StructuredBuffer<float4>). Lazily builds the pipeline from the Rurix container,
  buffer_update's the planes, buffer_clear's each surface's count dword + the
  bitmask BEFORE opening its own compute list, binds the four structured buffers
  (t0 transforms / t1 planes / u0 commands / u1 visibility as
  UNIFORM_TYPE_STORAGE_BUFFER), packs the 48-byte b0, and dispatches
  ceil(instance_count/64).
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/forward_clustered/render_forward_clustered.cpp:
  a new backend == 2 call-site (sibling of the untouched shim path). Collects the
  frame's indirect MultiMeshes, builds the normal-negated 96-byte t1 planes
  payload (n_rurix = -normal, d_rurix = plane.d — the Godot Plane sign red line)
  and the 48-byte b0, resolves the transform/command RIDs, lazily allocates the
  Rurix visibility bitmask, and offers each to the module.

The container line (co-located under passes/gpu_culling/artifacts): a new HLSL
kernel gpu_culling_rd_native.hlsl (frustum planes moved to a t1
StructuredBuffer<float4>, b0 shrunk 144 -> 48 bytes so it fits the RD 128-byte
root-constant window; the 144-byte shim b0 is rejected as push_constant_too_large
and cannot drive an RD container), a Rurix-owned RTS0 via the new
emit_grx015_gpu_culling_rd_native_rts0 example, a descriptor layout, a
generate_rd_container.py PASS_REGISTRY entry (gpu_culling_rd_native), and
out/gpu_culling_rd_native.rd_container.bin (DXC + DXV green, verify_container
59/59).

Fail-closed everywhere: default backend == 0 (and empty container path) never
engages the cull; a failed record is a no-op (the CPU-written command count
survives). Additive pass — no native Godot compute pass is replaced. Because the
cull is conservative (never culls a visible instance), the on-screen image is
identical to native; only the GPU draw-side instance count is reduced.
RXGD_ABI_VERSION unchanged (no C ABI struct change, no RxGdCaps.flags bit;
bridge-independent). No performance claim is made.
